Description:
- Express: backend framework
- Morgan: logging middlewares for backend
- Helmet: Security for web (Needed more research on)
- Compress: reduce file size when uploading to webs

Syntax wise:
- npm init: initialize existing / create new npm package
- npm i express
- npm i morgan --save-dev
- npm i helmet --save-dev
- npm i compression --save-dev
- curl.exe http://localhost:3055
- curl.exe http://localhost:3055 --include

Folder created:
- src: glueing things together
- src/configs
- src/controllers
- src/modals
- src/services
- src/utils
Files created:
- .env
- src/app.js
- .gitignore (node_modules, .env)

Notes:
- flag --save is unnecessary because on node 5.0.0, dependencies
are saved automatically
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/19578796/what-is-the-save-option-for-npm-install
